<div type="definition">
<p>CHANGE from SLEEP so as to BEGIN to be AWARE (AND LEAVE ONES BED).</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general word for waking up is wù 寤 (ant. mèi 寐 "fall fast asleep").</p>
<p>2. Jué 覺 (ant. meng 夢 "be deep asleep") refers to waking up, often after a dream.</p>
<p>3. Xīng 興 (ant. wò 臥 "sleep") refer to rising in the morning.</p>
<p>NB: Xǐng 醒 "wake up" is post-Han (TANG). In pre-Han times the word means "sober up".</p>
        </div>
